  <li><b><i><font color="#C86F02"><font size=+1>Quote of the Day</font></font></i></b></li>
</ul>
<blockquote> 
  <p>
  &quot;Oh, the disgrace of nature! Oh, the confusion of humanity! which makes 
  it that a man cannot be free without being a criminal. Must he be rendered a 
  slave in order to be virtuous? Yes, my brothers, that is our condition; our 
  passions require laws, our unjust and reckless desires must be restrained.&quot; 
  </p>
  <p> <i> &Eacute;loge de la Ma&ccedil;onnerie et des Ma&ccedil;ons; prononc&eacute; 
    par un Fr&egrave;re dans une Loge qui se tint &agrave; Paris le 25 Novembre 
    1744</i>, p. 11. Anonymous tract. From Jacob, Margaret C. <i>Living the Enlightenment</i>. 
    New York, NY: OUP, 1991. Jacob's translation, p. 6. </p>
</blockquote>
